# === v26 STOCK ASUS WEB STACK (the open-OS serves :80 via /jffs/webui/webui) ==
# CONFIRMED LIVE-DEAD: :80 is served by /jffs/webui/webui (webui-go, its own
# /jffs/webui/www); the stock /usr/sbin/httpd is NOT running; nothing references
# rootfs /www at runtime; webui lives on /jffs (NOT in this rootfs). The stock
# ASUS UI tree + httpd are pure dead weight here.
#
# --- the ENTIRE stock ASUS UI tree (~34.0 MB raw) ---------------------------
# Includes the lang dicts (/www/*.dict), cgi-bin, SDN/aimesh/VPN/device-map/
# ajax/js/images/mobile templates — ALL stock-web data, removed with the tree.
www
#
# --- stock web server (the C httpd ASUS rc would launch on :80/:443) --------
# usr/sbin/httpds is a symlink -> httpd (the https variant); both go.
usr/sbin/httpd
usr/sbin/httpds
#
# --- web-EXCLUSIVE library back-ref scan (full-rootfs DT_NEEDED + dlopen) ----
# Candidate web libs in the base: ONLY usr/lib/libwebapi.so and lib/libdisk.so
# exist (no libwebui/libwebdav/cgi-helper libs ship). BOTH are KEPT — NOT listed:
#   libwebapi.so  DT_NEEDED by: /sbin/rc, /sbin/wps_pbcd, /usr/sbin/httpd.
#                 rc is in the KEEP-set (config_switch/sync_apgx_to_wlunit) and
#                 DT_NEEDED libwebapi -> removing it would break rc load. KEEP.
#   libdisk.so    DT_NEEDED by: /sbin/rc, /sbin/wps_pbcd + the (removed) lighttpd
#                 /webdav/samba cluster. rc DT_NEEDED it -> KEEP (rc must load).
